How to execute multiple class files (TestNG based scripts) in Maven project?


testng.xml needs to be created and pom.xml needs to be updated with plugin configuration

create "src/main/resources" source folder and create file inside it. file name should be testng.xml and content should below

testng.xml:

<!DOCTYPE suite SYSTEM "http://testng.org/testng-1.0.dtd" >

<suite name="suiteName" >
  <test name="testName" >
    <packages>
      <package name="com.qa.tests" />
   </packages>
  </test>
</suite>


pom.xml should be updated with below plugin script.

      <build>
         <plugins>
            <plugin>
               <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
               <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
               <version>2.12.4</version>
               <configuration>
                  <suiteXmlFiles>
                     <suiteXmlFile>src/main/resources/testng.xml</suiteXmlFile>
                  </suiteXmlFiles>
               </configuration>
            </plugin>     
         </plugins>
      </build>
